more than ever before , this year has seen some pretty intense backlashes to the nominated films .
it 's an obvious escalation , given the outrage culture we 're all screaming our way through , and it 's often entirely , and refreshingly valid .
but will it affect who voters actually do they care about resurfaced allegations of domestic violence against gary oldman ?
do they believe the claims of plagiarism being leveled at the shape of water ?
do they agree that martin mcdonagh 's take on race in america is tone-deaf in three billboards outside ebbing , missouri ?
my guess = probably not .
